<section class="hero home" id="landing">
  <div class="hero-header has-text-centered">
    <div class="title">
      <h1> Let's <b>Archive.Earth</b></h1>
    </div>
        <div class="title">
      <i class="far fa-arrow-alt-circle-down"></i>
    </div>
    <img id="globe" src='<%= Routes.static_path(@conn, "/images/globe-300px.png") %>' alt="globe">

    <div class="parent folder" id="folder">
      <img class="folder-back" src='<%= Routes.static_path(@conn, "/images/rectangle@2x.png") %>' alt="folder-back">
      <img class="over-image folder-front" src='<%= Routes.static_path(@conn, "/images/rectangle-front.png") %>' alt="over-image">
      </span>
    </div>
  </div>

</section>

<section> 
<div class="section container has-text-centered">
      <p class="title">An open platform for collective environmental memory.</p>
      <article class="media notification has-background-white">
        <p class="has-text-centered">Current systems to store environmental knowledge on computers are fragile and vulnerable to interference. That is why Archive.Earth was created, as a platform to collect, store, protect and share environmental research responsibly. We want to ensure scientists have tools to collaborate and communicate their findings with each other and the public.<br>
        <strong>How will we do this?</strong> Archive.Earth works with existing communities and groups to curate high quality, trusted information useful for democratic governance, scientific reproducibility, and empowering  ‘planetary-scale’ innovation. 
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
</section>


		<!-- .section -->
