									<h1 class="title is-size-4">Submit</h1>
									<p class="is-size-5">
                  ANYONE can submit information (maps, documents, images, data, etc) to be stored permanently.<br>A small one time fee will apply, but can be covered by a donor or internal funding programs.
									</p>
								</div>
							</div>
						</article>
					</div>
          	<div class="column">
						<article class="section">
							<figure class="has-text-centered">
								<span class="icon is-large">
									<img src='<%= Routes.static_path(@conn, "/images/archive_earth_archive_icon.svg") %>'> 
								</span>
							</figure>
							<div class="has-text-centered">
								<div class="content">
									<h1 class="title is-size-4">Review</h1>
									<p class="is-size-5">
										If no curation is sought, archiving occurs as soon as possible, operating 24h/day.<br> Quality assurance or subsidy requests are reviewed by appointed content teams.
									</p>
								</div>
							</div>
						</article>
					</div>
          	<div class="column">
						<article class="section">
							<figure class="has-text-centered">
								<span class="icon is-large">
									<img src='<%= Routes.static_path(@conn, "/images/archive_earth_cited_icon.svg") %>'> 
								</span>
							</figure>
							<div class="has-text-centered">
								<div class="content">
									<h1 class="title is-size-4">Cite</h1>
									<p class="is-size-5">
										Once stored, data will be viewable “as-published” forever. In the case of open-ended collections, data will be automatically updated.<br>Whenever possible content is viewable in a browser, as well as machine-exportable (API).
									</p>
								</div>
							</div>
						</article>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>
